## Private Member Functions

### getSuperRegDestIfDead() {#ada7c98d96b2704e903620a0085af1fb8}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Register FixupBWInstPass::getSuperRegDestIfDead (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; OrigMI) const</>}>
This returns the 32 bit super reg of the original destination register of the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> passed in, if that super register is dead just prior to <code>OrigMI</code>.

Check if after <code>OrigMI</code> the only portion of super register of the destination register of <code>OrigMI</code> that is alive is that destination register.

Otherwise it returns <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/utils/mem2reg-cpp/#a6fde3eb6ca09ddf2fd76432176d817bb">Register()</a>.

If so, return that super register in <code>SuperDestReg</code>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86fixupbwinsts-cpp/#l00084">84</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86fixupbwinsts-cpp">X86FixupBWInsts.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
